fields.name: Crossfit for beginners
fields.description: Crossfit is the most popular strength and conditioning program in the world. Achieving a well-rounded fitness, while doing one of our fun workouts, leads to increased functional strength and flexibility. Our online program has everything you need to get started with crossfit at home, learn proper form on every exercise, track your progress over time and give you access to our coaches through live chat.

fields.name: Crossfit for Intermediate
fields.description: Crossfit is an intense fitness program that uses a combination of gymnastics, calisthenics (body weight exercises), Olympic weightlifting and other functional movements performed at high intensity. The CrossFit program has been developed by designing hundreds of different workouts with a large number of variations. These workouts are called 'Workouts of the Day' or WODs. fields.name: Calisthenics at home
fields.description: Calisthenics is a fitness training method developed by author and athlete Calum von Moger that requires no equipment to get in shape. It's the easiest way to get into incredible shape, while saving time and money. Thousands of people worldwide have already achieved their goals using Calisthenics, and you can too!

fields.name: Calisthenics Next Level
fields.description: Calisthenics is the best way to stay fit in 2021. It's about strength, movement and body control. It's not just a workout but it's a lifestyle that teaches you how use your body to the fullest.

fields.name: Calisthenics All Out
fields.description: Calisthenics is a simple and effective training system that builds strength, agility and endurance. It's a great alternative to traditional weight-lifting or bodybuilding. There are also no expensive gym memberships required, since all you need is your own bodyweight.
